{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'cat package.json'","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"name\": \"codex-managed-agent\",\n  \"displayName\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent\",\n  \"description\": \"Manage Codex agent threads inside VS Code with search, lifecycle actions, inspector views, and local dashboard integration.\",\n  \"version\": \"0.0.2\",\n  \"publisher\": \"harzva\",\n  \"icon\": \"media/codex-agent.png\",\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"preview\": true,\n  \"repository\": {\n    \"type\": \"git\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/Harzva/codex-managed-agent.git\"\n  },\n  \"homepage\": \"https://github.com/Harzva/codex-managed-agent\",\n  \"bugs\": {\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/Harzva/codex-managed-agent/issues\"\n  },\n  \"galleryBanner\": {\n    \"color\": \"#08111f\",\n    \"theme\": \"dark\"\n  },\n  \"engines\": {\n    \"vscode\": \"^1.90.0\"\n  },\n  \"extensionKind\": [\n    \"workspace\"\n  ],\n  \"categories\": [\n    \"Other\"\n  ],\n  \"keywords\": [\n    \"codex\",\n    \"agent\",\n    \"dashboard\",\n    \"thread-manager\"\n  ],\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"package\": \"npx @vscode/vsce package\",\n    \"publish:vsix\": \"npx @vscode/vsce package\",\n    \"publish:marketplace\": \"npx @vscode/vsce publish\"\n  },\n  \"activationEvents\": [\n    \"onView:codexAgent.sidebar\",\n    \"onView:codexAgent.bottom\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.openPanel\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.openPanelBeside\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.showSidebar\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.showBottomPanel\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.maximizeDashboard\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.movePanelToNewWindow\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.openExternal\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.refreshPanel\",\n    \"onCommand:codexAgent.startServer\"\n  ],\n  \"main\": \"./extension.js\",\n  \"contributes\": {\n    \"configuration\": {\n      \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"codexAgent.baseUrl\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"default\": \"http://127.0.0.1:8787/\",\n          \"description\": \"Base URL for the running Codex-Managed-Agent web app.\"\n        },\n        \"codexAgent.autoStartServer\": {\n          \"type\": \"boolean\",\n          \"default\": true,\n          \"description\": \"Automatically start the local Codex-Managed-Agent FastAPI service when the panel opens and the server is not reachable.\"\n        },\n        \"codexAgent.pythonPath\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"default\": \"\",\n          \"description\": \"Optional Python executable used to launch the local Codex-Managed-Agent server. Leave empty to auto-detect .venv/bin/python3 or use python3.\"\n        },\n        \"codexAgent.serverRoot\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"default\": \"\",\n          \"description\": \"Optional absolute path to the Codex Manager server root directory that contains the Python package folder `codex_manager/`.\"\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"commands\": [\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.openPanel\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Open Dashboard\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.openExternal\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Open in Browser\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.showSidebar\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Show in Sidebar\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.showBottomPanel\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Show in Bottom Panel\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.openPanelBeside\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Open to Side\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.maximizeDashboard\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Full Screen\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.movePanelToNewWindow\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Move to New Window\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.refreshPanel\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Refresh Panel\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"command\": \"codexAgent.startServer\",\n        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Start Local Server\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"viewsContainers\": {\n      \"activitybar\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"codexManagedAgentSidebar\",\n          \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent\",\n          \"icon\": \"media/codex-agent.svg\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"panel\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"codexManagedAgentPanel\",\n          \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent\",\n          \"icon\": \"media/codex-agent.svg\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"views\": {\n      \"codexManagedAgentSidebar\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"webview\",\n          \"id\": \"codexAgent.sidebar\",\n          \"name\": \"Dashboard\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"codexManagedAgentPanel\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"webview\",\n          \"id\": \"codexAgent.bottom\",\n          \"name\": \"Dashboard\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"menus\": {\n      \"view/title\": [\n        {\n          \"command\": \"codexAgent.refreshPanel\",\n          \"when\": \"view == codexAgent.sidebar || view == codexAgent.bottom\",\n          \"group\": \"navigation\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"command\": \"codexAgent.openPanel\",\n          \"when\": \"view == codexAgent.sidebar || view == codexAgent.bottom\",\n          \"group\": \"navigation\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"command\": \"codexAgent.maximizeDashboard\",\n          \"when\": \"view == codexAgent.bottom\",\n          \"group\": \"navigation\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' ROADMAP.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Codex-Managed-Agent Long-Range Roadmap\n\nThis roadmap is the spine. It should stay short.\n\nUse it to answer:\n\n- what the main milestones are\n- what order we should execute them in\n- which task-plan file owns the concrete work\n\nDetailed work belongs in `task-plans/*.md`.\n\n## North Star\n\nMake `Codex-Managed-Agent` a dependable VS Code control surface for multi-thread Codex work:\n\n- stable enough for daily use\n- structured enough to keep evolving\n- fast enough to feel responsive\n- clear enough that new features do not collapse back into one giant file\n\n## Product Principles\n\n- **One interactive board**\n- **Server-aware, not server-fragile**\n- **Small, composable host modules**\n- **Board first, chrome second**\n- **Persistent memory**\n\n## Milestones\n\n### Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\n\nGoal:\n\n- keep the extension modular and reviewable\n\nRelated plans:\n\n- host/module cleanup is already largely completed\n- continue only when new architectural drift appears\n\n### Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\n\nGoal:\n\n- make board interaction intentional, smooth, and predictable\n\nPrimary plan:\n\n- `task-plans/board-interaction-quality-task-plan.md`\n\n### Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\n\nGoal:\n\n- make the extension useful as memory and workflow guidance, not only a launcher\n\nPrimary plan:\n\n- `task-plans/insight-and-guidance-task-plan.md`\n\n### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\n\nGoal:\n\n- make loop, background continue, and Codex visibility control trustworthy\n\nPrimary plans:\n\n- `task-plans/operational-reliability-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/codex-visibility-control-task-plan.md`\n\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\n\nGoal:\n\n- keep releases understandable, repeatable, and maintainable\n\nRelated plans:\n\n- release and doc quality work should stay aligned with the current architecture and priority docs\n\n## Delivery Order\n\n### Priority 1 — Must Stabilize First\n\n- `task-plans/board-interaction-quality-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/operational-reliability-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/codex-visibility-control-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/cross-path-unified-management-task-plan.md`\n\n### Priority 2 — Workflow Multipliers\n\n- `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/insight-and-guidance-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/no-editor-first-workflows-task-plan.md`\n\n### Priority 3 — Multi-Agent Expansion\n\n- `task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/claude-codex-team-space-task-plan.md`\n\n### Priority 4 — Ecosystem Extensions\n\n- `task-plans/wechat-bot-background-service-task-plan.md`\n- `task-plans/html-ppt-visual-extensions-task-plan.md`\n\n## Working Rule\n\nWhen new work appears:\n\n1. decide which priority bucket it belongs to\n2. attach it to an existing `task-plan` if possible\n3. create a new `task-plan` only when the work introduces a new delivery track\n4. keep `ROADMAP.md` as the index, not the implementation dump\n\n## Immediate Focus\n\nCurrent focus remains:\n\n- `task-plans/board-interaction-quality-task-plan.md`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
